results.name: Product of sums of the multisets of prime indices of each prime index of 2 * n + 1.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798.
formula: Fully multiplicative with a(prime(n)) = A056239(n), restricted to odd n.
example: 91 has prime indices {4,6} with prime indices {{1,1},{1,2}} with sums {2,3} with product a(45) = 6.
